summary: This is a transcript of FBI Special Agent [REDACTED]'s testimony before a federal grand jury in West Palm Beach on April 24, 2007. The testimony concerns a victim/witness, [REDACTED], who was granted immunity to testify, and discusses her prior interview with Palm Beach Police in fall 2005 where she was initially cooperative until informed she could face charges for bringing girls to Jeffrey Epstein.

keyFacts: A key witness, [REDACTED], was granted immunity by a federal judge on April 16, 2007, to testify before the grand jury investigating Jeffrey Epstein.
The witness [REDACTED] was a minor when she met Epstein and, according to police, later brought other girls to him, leading to potential charges against her.
During a Palm Beach Police interview in fall 2005, [REDACTED] was initially cooperative until police informed her she could face charges, causing her to seek an attorney.
The immunity order is sealed and restricts disclosure of its existence to only the witness, her counsel, grand jurors, prosecutors, and involved law enforcement.
The document reveals the grand jury was actively investigating Epstein in April 2007, with law enforcement coordinating witness testimony under grant of immunity.
